    "program": {
        "program_id": 8,
        "acronym": "BSAP",
        "title": "Bachelor of Science in Applied Physics",
        "career": "UGRD",
        "college": "CAS",
        "description": "The BS Applied Physics program aims to provide sufficient background knowledge, perspectives, and training to enable students to explore the practical implications of physics and extend the boundaries of what we know about the universe. Students of the program will learn how to apply the principles and methods of physics to solve practical problems or to extend our knowledge in physics and the other sciences. Students may do research in the foundations of quantum mechanics, condensed matter theory, statistical physics, cosmology and particle physics, materials physics and engineering, optics and instrumentation, physics education and complex systems. Graduates of this four-year program are equipped to pursue advanced physics research, university physics teaching, graduate studies, and employment in physics-related jobs in academia, businesses, industry, or the government.",
